==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Physostigmine
<hw>Phy`so*stig"mine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid found in the Calabar bean (the seed of <spn>Physostigma
venenosum</spn>), and extracted as a white, tasteless, substance,
amorphous or crystalline; -- formerly called <altname>eserine</altname>,
with which it was regarded as identical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Physostomi</ent>⟦br⟧
